snippet: Two towers are rising at Riverside Center, an eight-acre development in the low West 60s near the Hudson River that is the last piece of the Riverside South mega-project.
abstract: Two new high-rises at Riverside Center, eight-acre development in the low West 60s near the Hudson River that is the last piece of the Riverside South mega-project, are putting a shiny stamp on land once crossed by Penn Central trains; buildings, which both have bold architectural styles, will add a public school and stores, and possibly a European-style food market and restaurant.
lead_paragraph: Two towers are rising at Riverside Center, an eight-acre development in the low West 60s near the Hudson River that is the last piece of the Riverside South mega-project.
